                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.60p2/28: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Latvia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Coleman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-01-12T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 12, 1928—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5. Legation’s No. 5, January 11, 1 p.m. Authorization of acceptance of Latvian
                    proposal regarding Article 27 of proposed treaty did <pb facs="0315" n="205"
                        xml:id="pg_205"/> not authorize omission of last paragraph of that Article.
                    Such omission was not proposed in Legation’s despatch No. 4408 of March 21,
                    1927, nor in Latvian memorandum enclosed therewith. Department understands
                    Article 27 will read like Article 26 of United States-Estonian Treaty. Please
                    correct spelling of “incumbency.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
